'''Donebach''' is a neighborhood of the village of [[Mudau]], [[Odenwald]], [[Germany]] and has 369 inhabitants. At Donebach, there is the [[Sender Donebach|longwave transmitter]] of [[Deutschlandfunk]] for broadcasting on 153&nbsp;kHz, whose antenna masts are with a height of 363 metres the second tallest [[architectural structure|structure]] of [[Germany]].

