{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2014}} {{Use British English|date=May 2014}} {{dablink|This article is about British magician Jeffery Atkins. For the American rapper Jeffrey Atkins see the entry for [[Ja Rule]]}}
'''Henry Jeffery Atkins''' (3 September 1919 – 19 March 2001) was a British [[Magician (illusion)|magician]]. He is cited as a major force in the [[International Brotherhood of Magicians]] (IBM) British Ring, for which he was honorary secretary and convention organizer for many years.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.magictimes.com/archives/2001/2001-03_19-25.htm | title = ''Magic Times archives'' 19-25 March 2001 | accessdate = 2007-02-27 }}</ref> He also served a term as international president of the IBM.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.magician.org.uk/?blogid=1&archive=2001-03 | title = ''The Magician'' weblog archive 2001-03 | accessdate = 2007-02-27}} and also {{cite web | url = http://www.magictricks.com/bios/whoswhoab.htm | title = Magicians' biographies A-B, ''Magictricks.com library'' | accessdate = 2007-02-27 }}</ref> As a performer he specialized in revivals or re-creations of antique magic.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.magictimes.com/archives/2001/2001-03_19-25.htm | title = ''Magic Times archives'' 19-25 March 2001 | accessdate = 2007-02-27 }}</ref> He made a number of appearances on national television in the United Kingdom. On one occasion he staged a revival of the [[Radium Girl]] illusion for the ''[[Paul Daniels|Paul Daniels Magic Show]]''. He is commemorated through the ''Jeffery Atkins memorial lecture'' held at the annual convention of the [http://www.britishring.org.uk British Ring of the IBM].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.magicweek.co.uk/backissues_0250-0299/0254.htm | title = ''Magic Week'' back issues Number 254 - 7 May 2005 | accessdate = 2007-02-27 }}</ref>
==Spelling== There is occasionally confusion over the spelling of Atkins' name. His obituary at the ''Magic Times'' website used the spelling Jeffery and it has been stated on the ''Genii magazine'' forum that this was the correct spelling, ''not'' Jeffrey.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://geniimagazine.com/forum/cgi-bin/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_topic;f=14;t=001409 | title = ''The Genii Forum'', 13 August 2003 | accessdate = 2007-02-27}}</ref>
