{{Japanese name|San'yūtei and Ai}}
{{Nihongo|'''6th Sanyutei Enraku'''|6代目 三遊亭 円楽|Rokudaime San'yūtei Enraku|born February 8, 1950}} is a Japanese [[rakugo]] [[comedian]] known for performing on the ''[[Shōten]]'' [[comedy]] show on [[Nippon TV]].

He was born {{Nihongo|'''Yasumichi Ai'''|會 泰通|Ai Yasumichi}} and currently uses Enraku as his [[stage name]]. He is known as a master of the Japanese comic art of rakugo, in which a single [[performer]] or [[Storytelling|storyteller]] appears on [[Stage (theatre)|stage]] and tells comedic stories to the audience.

While a student at [[Aoyama Gakuin University]], he began studying rakugo under [[San'yūtei Enraku V]].<ref name=PC>{{cite web|title=【三遊亭円楽さん】気になることはすぐ「ググる」|url=http://pc.nikkeibp.co.jp/article/interview/20140711/1136663/?rt=nocnt|website=PC Online|publisher=Nikkei Business|accessdate=23 January 2016|language=Japanese|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160208055154/http://pc.nikkeibp.co.jp/article/interview/20140711/1136663/?rt=nocnt|archivedate=8 February 2016|df=}}</ref> His first stage name was {{Nihongo|'''San'yūtei Rakutarō'''|三遊亭 楽太郎|San'yūtei Rakutarō}}, until he inherited his teacher's name in March 2010.<ref name=Asahi>{{cite web|title=「名人より達人目指す」 六代目三遊亭円楽襲名の楽太郎|url=http://www.asahi.com/showbiz/stage/rakugo/TKY201002260332.html|website=Asahi Digital|publisher=Asahi Shinbun|accessdate=23 January 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref>

He is a producer of the Hakata Tenjin Rakugo Matsuri, a rakugo festival held in [[Fukuoka city]] since 2007.

