{{For|the film|Tormenta (film)}}
{{Expand Portuguese|date=August 2018}}
{{Multiple issues|
{{Notability|date=June 2017}}
{{More citations needed|date=April 2008}}
}}

'''Tormenta''' is a [[Brazil]]ian [[campaign setting]] for [[role-playing game]]s that is played with [[D20 System]] or [[3D&T]] System. ''Tormenta'' is a [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] word that means "storm". A magic storm threatens the world's lives. It was created by [[Marcelo Cassaro]], [[Rogério Saladino]], and [[J. M. Trevisan]], and is published by [[Jambô]] Publisher since 2005. It is one of the most popular RPG games in Brazil.{{Citation needed|date=April 2008}} The scenario is Arton, the main continent that is "the known world". The coast is bad for sailing and therefore the seas are not explored.

==Official material==
*Adventure 3.5 (Publisher Talismã): The Release of Valkaria.
*Books [[3D&T]] (Publisher Talismã): Manual of Adventurer, Manual of Monsters, Tormenta 3D&T, The Realm Parts 1, 2 and 3 and [[Holy Avenger]] 3D&T.
*Books [[Twenty-sided polyhedral die|d20]] (Publisher Talismã): The Realm d20 and Holy Avenger d20. 
*Books 3.5 (Publisher Jambô): Player's Guide, Master's Guide, Arcane Academy, Vectora: City of the Clouds, The Pantheon, Tormenta area, Pirates & Gunners, and Galrasia: The Lost World.
*Comics: O Dado Selvagem (The Wild Dice), [[Dungeon Crawlers]], Holy Avenger, DBride and Ledd. 
*Magazines: DragonSlayer and Magazine Tormenta, and the editions 27, 44, 45, 47, 59, 77, 88, 103, 108, 110 and 111 of [[Dragão Brasil]].
*Novels: O Inimigo do Mundo (The Enemy of World), O Crânio e O Corvo (The Skull and the Crow), and O Terceiro Deus (The Third God), all by [[Leonel Caldela]].

